Very powerful Ruby topic 👌🔥
This is pure meta-programming.

Let’s understand class_eval vs instance_eval from absolute scratch.

🧠 Step 1 — What is eval in general?

eval means:

"Execute this block of code in a different context."

Ruby allows you to change what self is while executing code.

That’s what these methods do.

🎯 Core Difference (High-Level)
Method	Changes self to	Used to define
class_eval	The class	Instance methods
instance_eval	A specific object	Singleton methods

Now let’s break this slowly.

1️⃣ What is self?

Inside any Ruby code, there is a current object called:

self

When you change self, method definitions behave differently.

2️⃣ class_eval

class_eval evaluates code inside the class context.

It changes self to the class.

Example 1 — Add Instance Method Dynamically
class User
end

User.class_eval do
  def greet
    "Hello"
  end
end

u = User.new
puts u.greet
What happened?

Inside class_eval:

self becomes User

def greet defines an instance method

So all objects of User get it.

3️⃣ instance_eval

instance_eval evaluates code inside a specific object.

It changes self to that object.

Example 2 — Add Singleton Method
class User
end

u = User.new

u.instance_eval do
  def greet
    "Hello"
  end
end

puts u.greet

Works!

But:

User.new.greet

❌ Error

Because method was added only to that specific object.

That is called a singleton method.

🧠 Visual Difference
class_eval
User.class_eval

Adds method to:

User class → all instances
instance_eval
u.instance_eval

Adds method to:

Only object u
🔥 Very Important: self Difference
In class_eval
User.class_eval do
  puts self
end

Output:

User
In instance_eval
u.instance_eval do
  puts self
end

Output:

#<User:0x000...>

So self becomes the object itself.

🧠 Real Interview Explanation
class_eval

Opens class context

Adds instance methods

Used to modify classes dynamically

instance_eval

Opens object context

Adds singleton methods

Used to modify specific object

🚀 Practical Comparison
Case 1 — Modify Whole Class
class Product
end

Product.class_eval do
  def price_with_tax
    100 * 1.18
  end
end

All products now have price_with_tax.

Case 2 — Modify Only One Object
p1 = Product.new
p2 = Product.new

p1.instance_eval do
  def special_price
    50
  end
end

Now:

p1.special_price  # works
p2.special_price  # error
🔥 How Rails Uses This

Rails uses:

class_eval to dynamically add attribute methods

instance_eval in DSLs (like routes, validations, scopes)

Example style:

class MyDSL
  def initialize(&block)
    instance_eval(&block)
  end
end

This allows:

MyDSL.new do
  some_method
end

Because inside block, self becomes DSL object.

🧠 Simple Mental Model
class_eval

👉 "Open the class and add behavior to all objects."

instance_eval

👉 "Open this specific object and add behavior only to it."

🎯 One-Line Interview Answer

class_eval evaluates code in the context of a class and defines instance methods, while instance_eval evaluates code in the context of a specific object and defines singleton methods.

